The paper focuses on detecting low rapport during natural interactions in small groups using non-verbal behavior analysis. This involves analyzing facial expressions, hand motion, gaze, speaker turns, and speech prosody. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also uses computer vision techniques to analyze facial expressions, which suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the second likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing to analyze speech prosody, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also uses multi-view camera systems to record videos, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing temporal segments of interactions, which suggests cs.SD (Sound) as the fifth likely sub-category.
